'''Abraham Joseph ben Simon Wolf Menz''' was an eighteenth century [[rabbi]] and [[mathematician]] at [[Frankfurt]].

He wrote an elementary textbook on mathematics entitled ''Reshit Limmudim'', in three parts: "Kelale Handasah," the general rules of algebra; "Yesodot ha-Gemaṭriot," the elements of geometry; and "Yesod ha-Tekunah," on astronomy.<ref>{{Cite Jewish Encyclopedia|url=http://www.jewishencyclopedia.com/articles/10688-menz-abraham-joseph-ben-simon-wolf|title=Menz, Abraham Joseph ben Simon Wolf|first1=Gotthard|last1=Deutsch|first2=S. J.|last2=Levinson}}</ref>

